# Snyk policy — Kenjiri
# Documented acceptances per D17/D28 fix-and-rescan loop (2026-07-01).
version: v1.25.0
ignore:
  'python/PT':
    - '*':
        reason: >
          Two Low CWE-23 findings, both accepted after hardening. (1)
          persistence/paths.py: source is %LOCALAPPDATA%, an OS-managed
          per-user env var; code enforces absolute path, rejects '..'
          segments, canonicalizes via os.path.realpath and verifies
          prefix-containment of the app dir. No trust boundary is crossed
          (single-user offline game running as the same user). (2)
          tools/make_assets.py: dev-only build CLI whose purpose is writing
          assets to a caller-chosen directory on the developer's own
          machine; '..' segments rejected, path canonicalized. Snyk Code
          does not model custom validation as a python/PT sanitizer, so
          the flow remains flagged regardless. Re-evaluate at expiry.
        expires: 2027-01-01T00:00:00.000Z
